<subSubSection id="C311B0F9CA2DFFDEEEBDFF13402FFDDA" pageId="52" pageNumber="497" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BB4E372CA2DFFDEEEBDFF134081FE1F" pageId="52" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis id="B97F3F60CA2DFFDEEEBDFF134021FEAA" bold="true" box="[159,292,254,280]" pageId="52" pageNumber="497">Etymology</emphasis>
Name is derived from a local word meaning dragonfly or damselfly (noun in apposition). 
<heading id="D0FC541ECA2DFFDEEEBDFE794081FE1F" bold="true" box="[159,388,404,429]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="52" pageNumber="497" reason="6">
<emphasis id="B97F3F60CA2DFFDEEEBDFE794081FE1F" bold="true" box="[159,388,404,429]" pageId="52" pageNumber="497">Range and ecology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4E372CA2DFFDEEEBDFE55402FFDDA" pageId="52" pageNumber="497">
Discovered in forest 
<misspelling id="1400263F1935B0DEFF209728C2BC5D1D" pageNumber="497" type="misspelled">understory</misspelling>
around 
<number id="3DC3F155CA2DFFDEECA6FE5543ABFE60" box="[644,686,440,466]" pageId="52" pageNumber="497" value="360.0">360</number>
and 
<quantity id="4CF34E97CA2DFFDEECCCFE55423FFE60" box="[750,826,440,466]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="52" pageNumber="497" unit="m" value="400.0">400 m</quantity>
a.s.l. close to the large blackwater Itimbiri River (
<figureCitation id="1330FFF7CA2DFFDEEC2CFE30437DFE4A" box="[526,632,477,504]" captionStart="Photo 18" captionStartId="51.[782,849,1295,1319]" captionText="Photo 18. Forest near the mouth of the Itimbiri River in the Congo River in Congo-Kinshasa. Aciagrion bapepe and Ceriagrion obfuscans were found in the understory. Photo: KDBD (13 - v- 2010)" pageId="52" pageNumber="497">
Photo 
<number id="3DC3F155CA2DFFDEEC79FE30437DFE4A" box="[603,632,477,504]" pageId="52" pageNumber="497" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) in central Congo-Kinshasa, probably breeding in 
<misspelling id="1808A62668525B99E1EFEC11449A88DF" pageNumber="497" type="misspelled">floodwater</misspelling>
pools. Found with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B98F1CA2DFFDEECF9FDEF4036FDF0" authority="Pinhey, 1973" authorityName="Pinhey" authorityYear="1973" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Pseudagrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="52" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagasoides">
<emphasis id="B97F3F60CA2DFFDEECF9FDEF450EFDAF" box="[731,1035,514,541]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="497">
Pseudagrion 
<misspelling id="33F597DA9CD2DC71745CC85E11EFABED" pageNumber="497" type="misspelled">malagasoides</misspelling>
</emphasis>
Pinhey, 
<number id="3DC3F155CA2DFFDEEED9FDC54036FDF0" box="[251,307,552,578]" pageId="52" pageNumber="497" value="1973.0">1973</number>
</taxonomicName>
that, while not closely related, has a similar habitat and general appearance.
</paragraph>
